      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"8. QUINLEE BALE jumped from out wide and was game in defeat last start when a 2 length second (34.32) behind Paw Danny at this track. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Good form should continue. 4. BELAIR CROWN was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 5 lengths into third (34.52) at this track in a Grade 5 over 595m. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in three starts. Hard to beat again. 1. OUTSIDES was a narrow winner last time, jumping from this same box to score by a nose in a Grade 4/5 over 515m at this track. Key chance on best form. 7. ZIPPING SANDCHEZ cannot be dismissed although new to this distance.\",\"runners\":[8,4,1,7],\"exclusive\":false}",
